         <abstract>
            <p>Let $Z$ be the class of real-valued functions, defined and continuous on the closed interval $I = [-1, 1]$, such that $f(\pm 1) = 0$ and $|f(\xi) - 2f\{(\xi + \eta)/2\} + f(\eta)| \leqslant|\xi - \eta|$ for all $\xi$ and $\eta$ in $I$. Let $K = \sup_{f \in Z}\max_{x \in I}|f(x)|$. We will prove that $13/10 \leqslant K \leqslant 1014/779 &lt; 1.301669$.</p>
          </abstract>
